Sweat was pouring off the face of the man with the long white hair and beard. “Hell! it’s hot here!” he gasped. His companion – with the piercing eyes, hawk nose and trim goatee – said: “What do you expect? It’s Hell…” The white-haired one looked around in disbelief: “Every time I think I will wake and find it’s been a nightmare … but it’s not. “I told people religion was the opium of the masses and that places like Heaven and Hell are figments of the imagination. But I was wrong.” The goatee man said: “I understand, Herr Marx....